description: Command to configure global system parameters.
It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request.
The parameters for different commands are listed below:
setIgmpParameters (2): (optional, but at least one of them should be there)
sheIgmpControlProgramPreviewEnable (obsolete with R3.7M)
sheIgmpControlLogEnable (obsolete with R4.7M)
sheIgmpControlUploadEnable (obsolete with R4.7M)
setFtpParameters (3):
sheIgmpControlFtpRootDir
sheIgmpControlFtpIp (optional, not needed if a transfer profile is used)
sheIgmpControlFtpUser (optional, not needed if a transfer profile is used)
sheIgmpControlFtpPassword (optional, not needed if a transfer profile is used)
sheIgmpControlFtpUploadInterval
sheIgmpControlFileTransferProfile (new with R3.8M)
setIgmpPacketRateLimitUplink (9):
sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitUplink
setIgmpPacketRateLimitSubscriber (15):
sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitSubscriber
setIgmpLongTimeOnlineTime (16): -> obsolete with R4.7M
sheIgmpControlLongTimeOnlineTime
setIgmpEthernetAccessEnable (17):
sheIgmpControlEthernetAccessEnable
resetSubscriberPreviewCountAll (13): [NO_CONFIG-CHANGE]
manuallyUploadLog (14): [NO_CONFIG-CHANGE]
Notifications:
sheIgmpControlResult at the command ending in case of long running command.
The long running command refers to the case that sheIgmpUploadEnable
is changed from disable to enable. NE will verify the FTP connection at the
enabling moment. Besides, the RootDir is created if they do not exist yet.
EM should GET sheIgmpControlReqResult when the Response of the SET PDU
is received, and the error status is noError. If the value of
sheIgmpControlReqResult is comExecStarted(30), which means the SET operation
is a long running command, EM must issue another GET operation on
sheIgmpControlTimer. A timer should start on EM with the expire time equals
to the value of sheIgmpControlTimer. The sheIgmpControlResult trap is expected
to reach EM within the specified time.
When the trap is received by EM, EM can optionally GET
sheIgmpControlReqResult, sheIgmpControlStatus, and sheIgmpControlTimeStamp.

description: This parameter configure the valid file transfer profile in SHE-SECURITY-MIB.
Recommended for all new configurations, including FTP and SFTP.
For normal FTP transfer without data encryption -> profile is not mandatory, but recommended.
For filetransfer via SSH FTP (SFTP) -> profile is mandatory. Parameter should point to a profile
in sheSecurityConnectionProfileTable or sheSecurityDistributionProfileTable.
NOTE:
New parameter with R3.8M (only SFTP and FTP supported).
